# Competency question: "What deontic forces can a PURRDF norm carry, and is
# the vocabulary open?"
# Expected: at least obligation (must), prohibition (must not), permission
# (may), and recommendation (should) — the seeds of the OPEN DeonticModality
# vocabulary (#351, EPIC #348). There is no ought, only ought-according-to:
# every modality-bearing norm names its issuer (SHACL-enforced).

PREFIX purrdf: <https://blackcatinformatics.ca/purrdf/>

SELECT ?modality WHERE {
    ?modality a purrdf:DeonticModality .
}
ORDER BY ?modality
